net.maritimecloud.util.geometry

Class PositionReaderSimulator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.maritimecloud.util.geometry.PositionReaderSimulator

  • public final class PositionReaderSimulator
extends Object
    A simple builder for creating position readers that simulate simple sailing patterns.

    • Method Detail

      • forArea

        public PositionReader forArea(Area area)
        Creates a new simulated position reader. The simulated vessel will start at random position within the specified area. And then travel to another random position within the area. When it arrives at the position it will choose another random position within the area to travel to and so on.
        Parameters:
        area - the area to travel within
        Returns:
        a new position reader
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified area is null

      • forRoute

        public PositionReader forRoute(Position... positions)
        Creates a new simulated reader with the specified route. When the vessel reaches the last of the specified positions. It will sail the same route back. Continuing indefinitely.

        If the first position and the last position is equivalent the positions will be delivered as if the vessel is sailing in a circle. When the ship reaches the final position it will sail to position number 2 instead of sailing the same route back.

        Parameters:
        positions - each position for route
        Returns:
        a new simulated reader

      • setSpeedFixed

        public PositionReaderSimulator setSpeedFixed(double speed,
                                             SpeedUnit speedUnit)
        Sets a fixed speed for the vessel.

        If no speed is set the simulated position reader will use a variable speed between 1 and 40 knots.

        Parameters:
        speed - the speed of the vessel
        speedUnit - the unit of speed
        Returns:
        this builder
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the speed unit is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified speed is non positive
        See Also:
        setSpeedVariable(double, double, SpeedUnit)

      • setSpeedVariable

        public PositionReaderSimulator setSpeedVariable(double minSpeed,
                                                double maxSpeed,
                                                SpeedUnit speedUnit)
        Sets a variable speed for the vessel. Every time the vessel reaches a target position. It will change the speed to a random number between minimum speed and maximum speed.

        If no speed is set the simulated position reader will use a variable speed between 1 and 40 knots.

        Parameters:
        minSpeed - the minimum speed of the vessel
        maxSpeed - the maximum speed of the vessel
        speedUnit - the unit of speed
        Returns:
        this builder
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the speed unit is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified minimum speed is non positive or the max speed is than or equal to minimum speed
        See Also:
        setSpeedFixed(double, SpeedUnit)

      • setTimeSource

        public PositionReaderSimulator setTimeSource(LongSupplier timeSource)
        Sets the time source that is used to determine how long duration has passed between succint invocations of PositionReader.getCurrentPosition(). If no time source is set, System.currentTimeMillis() is used.
        Parameters:
        timeSource - the time source
        Returns:
        this builder
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified time source is null

      • setTimeSourceFixedSlice

        public PositionReaderSimulator setTimeSourceFixedSlice(long milliesIncrement)
        Sets a deterministic time source that increment the time with the specified amount of milliseconds every time.
        Parameters:
        milliesIncrement - the number of milliseconds that the ship will sail every time PositionReader.getCurrentPosition() is invoked
        Returns:
        this builder
